    "content": "<p>Two passive two-port networks P and Q are connected as shown in the figure. The impedance matrix of network P is $Z_P = \\begin{bmatrix} 40 \\Omega &amp; 60 \\Omega \\\\ 80 \\Omega &amp; 100 \\Omega \\end{bmatrix}$. The admittance matrix of network Q is $Y_Q = \\begin{bmatrix} 5 \\, \\text{S} &amp; -2.5 \\, \\text{S} \\\\ -2.5 \\, \\text{S} &amp; 1 \\, \\text{S} \\end{bmatrix}$. Let the ABCD matrix of the two-port network R in the figure be $\\begin{bmatrix} \\alpha &amp; \\beta \\\\ \\gamma &amp; \\delta \\end{bmatrix}$. The value of $\\beta$ in $\\Omega$ is ______________ (rounded off to 2 decimal places).</p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lxolylfi/6c580045-062e-493c-b7ae-ba84c5b1dfec/72d351e0-2fc1-11ef-9032-99cc6a311420/file-jaoe38c1lxolylfj.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lxolylfi/6c580045-062e-493c-b7ae-ba84c5b1dfec/72d351e0-2fc1-11ef-9032-99cc6a311420/file-jaoe38c1lxolylfj.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE EE 2024 Electric Circuits - Two Port Networks Question 2 English\">",
    "options": [],
    "correct_options": [],
    "answer": "-19.90TO-19.70",
    "explanation": null,
    "topic": null,
