    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>The admittance parameters of the passive resistive two-port network shown in the figure are</p>\n<p>$${y_{11}} = 5\\,S,{y_{22}} = 1\\,S,{y_{12}} = {y_{21}} =  - 2.5\\,S$$</p>\n<p>The power delivered to the load resistor $$R_L$$ in Watt is __________ (Round off to 2 decimal places).</p><p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lz2vpeq8/39b9eebe-005c-48ab-9177-9b0294c13219/bf20f410-4b66-11ef-b55e-311e0f7eb3bf/file-jaoe38c1lz2vpeq9.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lz2vpeq8/39b9eebe-005c-48ab-9177-9b0294c13219/bf20f410-4b66-11ef-b55e-311e0f7eb3bf/file-jaoe38c1lz2vpeq9.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE EE 2023 Electric Circuits - Two Port Networks Question 3 English\"></p>",
    "options": [],
    "correct_options": [],
    "answer": "237TO239",
    "explanation": "<p>Given two port network and Y-parameters are shown below,</p>\n\n<p>The power delivered to the load resistor $$R_L$$ in Watt is <strong></strong><strong></strong>__ (Round off to 2 decimal places).</p><p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lz2vpeq8/39b9eebe-005c-48ab-9177-9b0294c13219/bf20f410-4b66-11ef-b55e-311e0f7eb3bf/file-jaoe38c1lz2vpeq9.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lz2vpeq8/39b9eebe-005c-48ab-9177-9b0294c13219/bf20f410-4b66-11ef-b55e-311e0f7eb3bf/file-jaoe38c1lz2vpeq9.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE EE 2023 Electric Circuits - Two Port Networks Question 3 English Explanation 1\"></p>\n\n<p>$$ Y=\\left[\\begin{array}{cc} 5 &amp; -2.5 \\\\ -2.5 &amp; 1 \\end{array}\\right] S $$</p>\n\n<p>For $3 \\Omega$ resistor $Y$-parameter matrix is,\n\n<br><br>$\\left[Y_1\\right]=\\left[\\begin{array}{cc}\\frac{1}{3} &amp; \\frac{-1}{3} \\\\ \\frac{-1}{3} &amp; \\frac{1}{3}\\end{array}\\right]$ and given $\\left[Y_2\\right]=\\left[\\begin{array}{cc}5 &amp; -2.5 \\\\ -2.5 &amp; 1\\end{array}\\right]$</p>\n\n<p>Over all $[Y]$ parameter matrix is,</p>\n\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; {[Y]=\\left[\\begin{array}{cc} \\frac{1}{3} &amp; \\frac{-1}{3} \\\\ \\frac{-1}{3} &amp; \\frac{1}{3} \\end{array}\\right]+\\left[\\begin{array}{cc} 5 &amp; -2.5 \\\\ -2.5 &amp; 1 \\end{array}\\right]} \\\\ &amp; {[Y]=\\left[\\begin{array}{cc} \\frac{16}{3} &amp; \\frac{-8.5}{3} \\\\ \\frac{-8.5}{3} &amp; \\frac{4}{3} \\end{array}\\right]} \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n\n<p>$Y$-parameter equation,</p>\n\n<p>$$ I_1, I_2=f\\left(V_1, V_2\\right) $$</p>\n\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; I_1=\\frac{16}{3} V_1-\\frac{8.5}{3} V_2 ........(i) \\\\ &amp; I_2=-\\frac{8.5}{3} V_1+\\frac{4}{3} V_2 .........(ii) \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n\n<p>From the given circuit $V_1=20 \\mathrm{~V}$ for finding $V_{t h}$, output current</p>\n\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; I_2=0 \\\\\\\\ &amp; 0=-\\frac{8.5}{3} V_1+\\frac{4}{3} V_2 \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; \\frac{8.5}{3}(20)=\\frac{4}{3} V_2 \\\\\\\\ &amp; V_{t h}=V_2=\\frac{8.5 \\times 20}{4}=42.5 \\mathrm{~V} \\\\\\\\ &amp; R_{t h}=\\left.\\frac{V_2}{I_2}\\right|_{V_1=0 \\mathrm{~V}} \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n\n<p>From equation (ii)</p>\n\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; I_2=\\frac{4}{3} V_2 \\\\\\\\ &amp; R_{t h}=\\frac{V_2}{I_2} \\\\\\\\ &amp; R_{t h}=\\frac{3}{4} \\Omega \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n\n<p>Thevenin's equivalent circuit</p>\n\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lz2vx4ea/8fb14207-e367-41dd-9dda-445adf242f52/95a52ec0-4b67-11ef-9cd1-a7ceb0733e70/file-jaoe38c1lz2vx4fh.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lz2vx4ea/8fb14207-e367-41dd-9dda-445adf242f52/95a52ec0-4b67-11ef-9cd1-a7ceb0733e70/file-jaoe38c1lz2vx4fh.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE EE 2023 Electric Circuits - Two Port Networks Question 3 English Explanation 2\">\n\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; I_L=\\frac{42.5}{\\frac{3}{4}+6} \\\\\\\\ &amp; I_L=6.29 \\mathrm{~A} \\\\\\\\ &amp; P_L=I^2 R_L=(6.29)^2 6 \\\\\\\\ &amp; P_L=237.38 \\mathrm{~W} \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n\n<p>Hence, the correct answer is 237.38 .</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2023,
    "yearKey": "gate-ee-2023",
    "difficulty": null
  },
