    "content": "<p>$$ \\text { The input impedance, } Z_{\\text {in }}(s) \\text {, for the network shown is } $$</p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mh5z558c/9be64587-a661-4160-ba1d-fd3776b5567c/6ee4efc0-b176-11f0-a8fc-1beb57a635e8/file-jaoe38c1mh5z558d.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mh5z558c/9be64587-a661-4160-ba1d-fd3776b5567c/6ee4efc0-b176-11f0-a8fc-1beb57a635e8/file-jaoe38c1mh5z558d.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE EE 2021 Electric Circuits - Two Port Networks Question 1 English\">",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "<p>$\\frac{23 s^2+46 s+20}{4 s+5}$</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "<p>$6 s+4$</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "<p>$7 s+4$</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "<p>$\\frac{25 s^2+46 s+20}{4 s+5}$</p>"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "A"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>$$ \\text { Method } 1 \\text { : } $$<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mh5z549a/974f412e-3062-4acf-8a4e-f45b97c06ad9/6e245ee0-b176-11f0-a8fc-1beb57a635e8/file-jaoe38c1mh5z549b.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mh5z549a/974f412e-3062-4acf-8a4e-f45b97c06ad9/6e245ee0-b176-11f0-a8fc-1beb57a635e8/file-jaoe38c1mh5z549b.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE EE 2021 Electric Circuits - Two Port Networks Question 1 English Explanation\"></p>\n<p>Applying KVL in the loop 1,</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; V_1=4 I_1+6 s I_1+s I_2 \\\\ &amp; V_1=(4+6 s) I_1+s I_2 \\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,...(i)\\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>Applying KVL in the loop 2,</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; 5 I_2+4 s I_2+s I_1=0 \\\\ &amp; I_2=-\\frac{s I_1}{4 s+5} \\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,...(ii)\\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned}So,\\,\\,\\, &amp; V_1=(4+6 s) I_1+s\\left[-\\frac{s I_1}{4 s+5}\\right] \\\\ &amp; \\frac{V_1}{I_1}=4+6 s-\\frac{s^2}{4 s+5} \\\\ &amp; \\frac{V_1}{I_1}=\\frac{24 s^2+16 s+20+30 s-s^2}{4 s+5} \\\\ &amp; \\frac{V_1}{I_1}=Z_{i n}(s)=\\frac{23 s^2+46 s+20}{4 s+5} \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>Hence, the correct option is (A).</p>",
