    "content": "Two passive two-port networks are connected in cascade as shown in figure. A voltage source is\nconnected at port 1.\n<img alt=\"GATE EE 2017 Set 1 Electric Circuits - Two Port Networks Question 16 English\" src=\"https://gateclass.cdn.examgoal.net/examside/questions/3f56efba53dfe453dfbd0e03ce94e39caf5888661b07c5d9a6b64a23c4752fe4.jpg\" style=\"text-align:center;max-width:100%;height:auto;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n$$\\begin{array}{l}Given:\\\\V_1=A_1V_2+B_1I_2\\\\I_1=C_1V_2+D_1I_2\\\\V_2=A_2V_3+B_2I_3\\\\I_2=C_2V_3+D_2I_3\\end{array}$$\n<p>$$A_1,\\;B_1,\\;C_1,\\;D_1,\\;A_2,\\;B_2,\\;C_2,\\;and\\;D_2$$ are the generalized circuit constants. If the Thevenin equivalent\ncircuit at port 3 consists of a voltage source V<sub>T</sub> and impedance Z<sub>T</sub> connected in series, then</p>",
